Package entity

Class Tweet

  • java.lang.Object
    • entity.Tweet
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<Tweet>
    public class Tweet
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<Tweet>
    Tweet entity is designed based on columns on dataset excel file, and aim to encapsulate data in Model layer and Controller layer.

    Inside this entity, following attributes are used to implement sorting operation: favs, rts, followers. Tweets would be ranked based on the sum of:

    1. number of users who like the tweet (Favs)
    2. number of users who re-tweet the tweet (RTs)

    In order to visualize this object, toString() method is overrided and all of its attributes could be printed out.

    Note: For the compareTo(Object o) method, it doesn't follow the conventions that for object which is literally bigger than itself, it will return -1. On the contrast, it will return 1 so that when ordered data structures such as TreeSet would have the biggest element on the top.
